(2588, 1011, 2588, NULL, 288, 'php und regul?re Ausdr?cke', 'Hallo,\r\n\r\npa?t zwar nicht ganz in dieses Forum, dennoch sind ja im Buch die Fallstricke zwischen PHP-Formularen und strings angesprochen.\r\nVorab:\r\nIch versuche eine Pa?wortgenerierung zu bauen, insofern der User sich selbst ein Pa?wort \'baut\'. In Rahmen dessen bin ich auf folgendes Problem gesto?en und meine bisherigen Recherchen waren fruchtlos.\r\nBeschreibung der Aufgabe: \r\nAfter reading the book \'regular Expressions\' from Jeffrey E.F. Friedl I tried to solve\r\nthe following problem (would it better to say :term of reference or Task position) in the script language PHP:\r\n$non_ascii_7 = \"[\\x7b- \\xff]*\";\r\nor the expression = \"/[\\x7b-\\xff]*/\"\r\n//// \"/[\\x00-\\x21]*/\"\r\n\r\necho \"7. test for regular expressions <br>\";\r\n    if((ereg($non_ascii_7, $string0))) //if its true\r\n	{\r\n    echo \"this mean it is not good for this string   \". $non_ascii_7. \"<br>\";\r\n	}\r\nI only get a error-message:\r\nWarning: ereg() [function.ereg]: REG_ERANGE in /home/wspalter/public_html/nuerversuch.php on line 50\r\nthis mean it is good for a eMails tring /[S-?]*/\r\nAs a beginner in PHP and regular expressions, I did not find the mistake.\r\n\r\nAs a beginner in PHP and regular expressions, I did not find the mistake.\r\nIn the Manuel on www.zend.com I could read the regular expressions in PHP agrees usually with which in  Perl.\r\n\r\nExcuse my terrible English although I am Beatles fan.\r\n\r\nThank you very much in advance\r\n\r\nGu?', '2003-08-27 09:23:43'),
