(2671, 1001, 318, 408, 897, 'Run-time error 13 \'type mismatch\'', 'I received this error when I tried to run a particular program I had donwloaded from the net.  It stopped my Google from working, I lost access to my File Search and was prevented from accessing a number of files on my PC.  I run Windows XP Pro and Office 2003.  I have a number of clean up programs, such as Norton System Works 2003, Reg Scrubber, Ad Aware 6 and so on.  \r\n\r\nNone of them could help.  I tride changing decimals in the Control Panel setup as suggested by one person.  But a lot of the suggestions were just gobbledegook to me not being a technical person.  All I wanted to do was get rid of the damn problem.  \r\n\r\nThen someone said that it was probably a corrupt driver and I might need to update.  So I downloaded a little utility called WinDriver and did a check.  It found 4 drivers that needed updating (not microsoft ones) I updated them and re-booted.\r\n\r\nTaking a deep breath I started clicking away.  Much to my relief the Run Time Error 13 mismach screen did not come back, all my files were accessible and I even had my File Search back.  I have not tried loading my Google yet, that is next, but I am satisfied that the answer looks like it lay with a driver corruption which the update seemed to have solved.  But only time will tell if that is the case.\r\n\r\nPerhaps some clever little genius out there could figure out a small program to seek out and find this damaging corruption or whatever it is and give a solution.  It almost cost me a complete Format again and the risk of losing everything not including the inconvenience of having to do the work and re-load everything.  \r\n\r\nSo my suggestion is, if all else fails. Check your program drivers and update as necessary.\r\n\r\nLet me know if it works and or if you find a different or better solution please.\r\n\r\nTony Sedgwick\r\ntony@portlandservices.com', '2003-10-22 15:05:40'),
