(2766, 1001, 2766, NULL, 287, 'Using concat function in M$ SQL', 'Hi,\r\n\r\nim trying to convert the database of a CMS, based on M$-SQL, to MySQL. I was so happy to find your amazing Skript. \r\nEverything seemed to work fine.... \r\n\r\nFirst problem was, some table content couldnt be imported by mysql  throwing an syntax error (always something starting with 0x) \r\nI could \"fix\" this by deleting the suspicious data fields in the Dump.\r\nSo i lost some data, but thats ok. I can live with that.\r\n\r\nBut the problem im facing right now is even more worse.\r\nThe CMS used the concat function to generate its document keys....\r\ne.g.\r\nconcat(\'somestring\' + \'anotherstring\')\r\ni can find this code in an varchar field.\r\n\r\nbut after conversion with the mssql2mysql the corresponding field contains only\r\n\\\'somestring\\\'\r\n\r\nno more concat.\r\nAny suggestions where i can catch this in the script?\r\nI dont want to have to change 300 lines of code manually...\r\n:-(\r\n\r\nthanx.\r\n\r\nJo', '2003-11-17 12:50:10'),
