(3348, 1007, 2719, 2719, 513, 'RedHat 9.0 + AVM B1 + Hylafax', 'I did experience the same problems on Fedora Core 2 with Kernel 2.6.6 and was able to solve this with the help of the AVM-B1 mailinglist by applying the patch from http://www.sommrey.de/capi4hylafax/capi4hylafax-01.02.02-jo.patch .\r\n\r\nThe problem is related to the posix-thread library under the 2.6 kernel. More\r\ninformation about this (in German) can be found on\r\nhttp://groups.google.de/groups?q=%22%2Bwww.sommrey.de/capi4hylafax%\r\n22&hl=de&lr=&ie=UTF-8&selm=c1aiti%24uc0%241%40eisbaer.bawue.de&rnum=1 .', '2004-06-14 11:05:14'),
